AxB = {(1,2), (1,3), (2,2), (2,3)}
BxA = {(2,1), (2,2), (3,1), (3,2)}

As we can see, AxB and BxA are not equal, since they have different elements. This shows that the Cartesian product of two sets is not commutative with respect to intersection.

