Now, we can find the set D by subtracting the elements of A from the universal set U:

D = U - A = {6, 7, 8, 9, 10}

Now, we can find B and C using the expressions we derived earlier:

B = D ∪ {6, 7} = {6, 7, 8, 9, 10} ∪ {6, 7} = {6, 7, 8, 9, 10}
C = D ∪ {8} = {6, 7, 8, 9, 10} ∪ {8} = {6, 7, 8, 9, 10}

